data.title: Investiture of Haakon VII, King of Norway with the Order of the Garter, 1906
data.meta_description: The Court Circular reported that on Tuesday, 13 November, 1906 at Windsor, the King had held a Chapter of the Garter at 7.30 oclockâ€¦ in the Castle, for the purpose of investing his Majesty The King of Norway with the Insignia of this Most Noble Order. The ceremony was witnessed by the following already assembled in the Throne Room: The Queen of Norway, the Princess of Wales, Princess Victoria, Princess Christian of Schleswig-Holstein, Princess Louise, Duchess of Argyll, the Duchess of Connaught,...
